title: Disturbed - Indestructible
description:
ndestructible is the fourth studio album by American rock band Disturbed. The album was officially released on June 2, 2008[1] by Reprise Records,[2] with opening sales of 253,000 units, which beat the first-week sales of the band&#039;s previous album Ten Thousand Fists.[3] The album is also the first self-produced effort by the band, without producer Johnny K.[2] Indestructible is Disturbed&#039;s third consecutive #1 debut on the Billboard 200, and it remained in the Top 10 on the Billboard 200 for five consecutive weeks.[2] Only six other rock bands have accomplished three consecutive #1 debuts, including Dave Matthews Band, Metallica, Pearl Jam, Staind, U2, and Van Halen. [4] Indestructible was certified Gold in the United States by the RIAA on July 17, 2008, shipping over 500,000 copies.
